6.	Brief the difference between Class and Struct. Also, provide some information on when to use them.

Class: Class is a reference type and its object is created on the heap memory.
Class can create a subclass that will inherit parent's properties and methods.
A class has all members private by default.Sizeof empty class is 1 Byte

Structure: structure is a value type and its object is created on the stack memory.
Structure does not support the inheritance.A struct is a class where members are public by default.
Sizeof empty structure is 0 Bytes
